Abstract: Provides relative to the membership of the board of commissioners for the
Central La. Juvenile Detention Center Authority.
Present law provides for the board of commissioners of the Central La. Juvenile Detention
Center Authority.
Present law further provides for membership of the board of commissioners as follows:
(1) Two commissioners appointed by the judges exercising juvenile jurisdiction within
the participating parishes.
(2) Two commissioners appointed by the sheriffs of the participating parishes.
(3) One commissioner appointed by the chiefs of police of municipalities within the
participating parishes.
(4) Two commissioners appointed by the district attorneys with jurisdiction in the
participating parishes.
Proposed law amends present law to change the membership of the board of commissioners
to the following individuals who are qualified electors, domiciled and residing within their
respective parishes, and jointly appointed by the chief judge and district attorney for their
respective judicial districts and the sheriff of their respective parishes as follows:
